Ask HN: Tech stack suggestion for a simple desktop app
text:
Hello HN,

I want to develop a simple desktop application for a non-profit, that will be used to store monetary contribution data from donors.

There should be a facility to generate receipts, get monthly reports and query the data offline.

The software will be running in a Windows based Desktop machine. The desktop machine is low end (1 GB RAM).

Ask HN: What app or app feature do you wish existed?
text:
I'll go first...

I really wish I could have immersive routes on a treadmill or workout bike. This could be via a simple 360 degree trail/route or even in the more immersive VR headset. The treadmill inclines and gradients would auto adjust as i go through it. I think i might even engage more with ads this way.

For example, I would like to be able to run through NYC or Paris or London with an all around view of the stores ans streets that i am passing through and feel the inclines and corners etc. If a coffee shop or a store has a promotion or an offer, it could be marked on their storefront or something.

This could also encourage stores to 360 map their own store layout so that I can 'walk in' and purchase.

This is my app wish. I am not sure if such a thing exists already.

What app do you wish for?
